Final Decision: In its decision (Decision IPCC-LII.6), the Panel adopts the IPCC Gender Policy and Implementation Plan as contained in an annex to the decision. The IPCC Gender Policy has the objectives of:
- enhancing gender equality in IPCC processes, including promoting equal opportunities for all, regardless of gender, within the governance and execution of IPCC activities;
- a gender-inclusive environment, including striving to facilitate participation of those with child or elderly care responsibilities; and
- training and guidance, including raising awareness about gender-related issues and gender equality within the IPCC. The IPCC Gender Implementation Plan entails, inter alia, establishing the GAT, which will:
- oversee and monitor the implementation of actions detailed in the Gender Implementation Plan;
- propose, to the Panel, potential future refinements of the Gender Policy and the Implementation Plan as needed and at least at the beginning of each assessment cycle;
- serve as the point of contact for gender-related issues; and
- develop and implement a protocol and process for addressing complaints made in the context of the Gender Policy and Implementation Plan.

